entries.title: Endor System: Destroy the Evil Raider Tyrant
entries.split_quest_alert: \#pcontrast3 CorSec Command: < \#pcontrast1 Keep on the alert Captain, I don't like the looks of this. Our computers detect a rather large hyperspace surge. \#pcontrast3 >
entries.quest_target_d: Primary Objective, bring down at all costs
entries.quest_location_d: An area of Endor Space controlled by pirates
entries.quest_escort_d: Not to be taken lightly, these targets need to be destroyed as well
entries.failed_escape: Pilot! The target escaped! The mission is a failure! Return to your superior for further instruction.
entries.escort_wiped_out: \#pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < \#pcontrast1 All escorting craft have been destroyed \#pcontrast3 >
entries.escort_remaining: \#pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < \#pcontrast1 An escorting craft has been destroyed, %DI remain \#pcontrast3 >
entries.destroy_escort: \#pcontrast3 CorSec Command: < \#pcontrast1 You've destroyed the Tyrant. But we also need to get his cronies. Continue with your objective, Captain. \#pcontrast3 >
entries.assassinate_success: \#pcontrast3 CorSec Command: < \#pcontrast1 Ha! I knew you could do it, Captain. The mission is a success! \#pcontrast3 >
entries.arrival_phase_2: \#pcontrast3 CorSec Command: < \#pcontrast1 We've detected the target. It seems as if he's got his cronies with him. You better watch out. It's gonna be ugly. \#pcontrast3 >
entries.arrival_phase_1: \#pcontrast3 CorSecCommand: < \#pcontrast1 Captain , do you read me? Your target will arrive soon and you must be ready for a fight. This could get pretty dangerous. Good luck! \#pcontrast3 >
